This paper presents a new data structure for preprocessing a set of points in R^2 and answering range counting queries. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the data structures (cs.DS) and computational geometry (cs.CG) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the expected query time and optimal decision trees, which suggests that it may also belong to the information theory (cs.IT) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper involves analyzing the performance of the data structure, which could place it in the discrete mathematics (cs.DM) sub-category.
